headline: Jabil (JBL): Revisiting Valuation After A Strong Multi‑Year Share Price Run
summary: Jabil (JBL) has quietly turned into a strong compounder, with the stock up about 61% year to date and roughly 72% over the past year, far outpacing the broader market. See our latest analysis for Jabil. That strength is not a flash in the pan. With a 7 day share price return of 7.4% and a 5 year total shareholder return of around 471%, it signals momentum that investors still seem willing to back at roughly $229.94 per share.
